text: Victoria Alcock (born 13 May 1968), in London) is a British actress. ==Notable roles== Alcock played the prisoner Julie Saunders on the television drama series, Bad Girlshttp://www.essexchronicle.co.uk/Essex-Jailbreak-Prisoners- flee-Chelmsford-Prison/story-21018193-detail/story.html and Agnes Clarke in The House of Eliott.http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00y0dzw In January 2012, Alcock was cast as Lorraine Stevens (née Salter), the ex-prostitute mother of Mandy Salter (Nicola Stapleton), in the BBC soap opera EastEnders, reviving the role from Linda Henry, who starred as Salter until 1992. Her first episode was broadcast on 1 March. ==Filmography== ===Film=== {|class="wikitable" |- ! Year ! Film ! Role !
